- Drupal 8+ version detection improvements

---

## Quick Reference

**Build:** `go build -o goCmsCheck ./cmd/goCmsCheck`

**Test WordPress:** `./goCmsCheck --url example.com --output wp_report.txt`

**Test Drupal:** `./goCmsCheck --url http://drupal.test --all-modules --output drupal_report.txt`

**Color scheme:** Bold cyan (section headers), bold (labels), normal (data)
**Color library:** github.com/fatih/color v1.18.0 (go-colorable, go-isatty, golang.org/x/sys)
**Rate limiting:** 5 requests/second global limit
**Default output:** None (stdout only, use --output to save to file)
**Output modes:** Stdout (colored) | File (plain text, ANSI codes stripped)
**CMS detection:** Automatic (meta tags → HTML patterns → endpoint probe, WordPress priority)
